  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class Circle
extends mil.emp3.api.abstracts.Feature
implements org.cmapi.primitives.IGeoCircle
    This class implements a Circle feature. It requires a single coordinate that indicates the geographic position of the center of the circle.

        public Circle()

      • Circle

        public Circle(double radius)
        This constructor creates a circle with the indicated radius.
        Parameters:
        radius - The required radius in meters. If the radius is < 0 the absolute value is used. If the value is == 0, the default radius is used.

      • Circle

        public Circle(org.cmapi.primitives.IGeoCircle renderable)
        This constructor create a circle feature based on the GeoCircle object provided.
        Parameters:
        renderable - see IGeoCircle. If the GeoCircle does not have a radius it is set to the default radius.
